column5: Just wondering if anyone could give me a headsup on the conditions there. Cheers Jeff
was there on friday, loads of water on top of the ice. anywhere from 3 to 7 inch of  black ice but not sure now since Sat was rain/warm weather and today was cold  hope it helps a bit
my buddy was out getting people off the ice in Keswick all day
When? I was in Keswick on Friday from 11-6.
if it's like the gilford side when the temp dropped everything froze up great
Thanks guys ended up fishing off eastbourne. 4" in 62ft of wat. 2 herring both quickly released, a ton of perch and missed a laker 25ft down. Cheers Jeff
could you see open water out farther
No but north of me was all the refozen slush and I didn't venture out there. Maybe this weekend if it stays cold. Cheers Jeff
thanks for the info lets hope it stays cold
BP maybe?  I,ll take a drive out there friday.
Hopefully be out on IBP or willow beach this weekend.
I heard IBP only has 2" it would be nice if it had 5" but the weekend
No real cold temps this week and constant flurries.... we could follow Brian carrying his new auger..
